# Architecture boundaries

## Separation of concerns

| Layer | May call | Must not |
|-------|----------|----------|
| UI / routes | Services, actions, hooks | Direct DB, raw secrets |
| Service | Domain, repositories, external APIs | Render UI |
| Data access | Database, caches | Business policy |
| Domain | Pure logic, types | Framework imports |

## Cross-cutting rules

- Validate at **system boundaries** (API input, webhooks, forms)
- One source of truth per concept — no duplicate models diverging
- Prefer **composition** over deep inheritance
- New dependencies require justification (size, maintenance, license)
- Document non-obvious decisions in ADR or plan (use `system-design-tradeoffs`)

## Before large refactors

1. Run or propose `graphify` on affected area
2. Name target architecture (frontend / backend / agentic skill)
3. Phase the migration — no big-bang without approval
